I have been driving since the age of 15 (now I'm 17), and where I live (Greece) you're not allowed to take a driver's test till 18. The most exciting thing that has happened so far after 2500 or so kms is me going at 170km/h for a bit, and going on rally mountain roads to have fun. But I do feel you, sometimes city driving can suck major butt due to the fact that people tend to be less than smart most of the time. I can't wait to get my license, for, as it happens, I love driving!


Love these videos, keep them coming! :)
